eu.cqse.check.framework.typetracker

Class ScopedTypeLookup

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.cqse.check.framework.typetracker.ScopedTypeLookup

  • public class ScopedTypeLookup
extends java.lang.Object
    A scoped type lookup is an associative data structure that maps variable names to their type information. A scoped type lookup can create child lookups, that can shadow variables from the parent. Further imported namespaces are stored.

    • Method Detail

      • addAddtitionalParent

        public void addAddtitionalParent(ScopedTypeLookup parent)
        Adds an additional parent lookup. This is useful e.g. when declarations and implementations are separated in the code. Ignores null and this values.
        Throws:
        java.lang.AssertionError - in case the parent to be added is already a descendant of the current lookup, which would cause a circular lookup dependency.

      • getTypeInfo

        public TypedVariable getTypeInfo(java.lang.String variableName)
        Returns the type information for the given key. If the key is not found in this scoped lookup, the parent lookups will be searched recursively. If the key does not exist, null is returned.
